" 0 "" {TEXT -1 204 "5.  Three-dimensional plots.  Maple can also prov
ide representations for graphs of functions of two variables.  The gra
phs of such functions are surfaces in three-dimensional space.  The Ma
ple command is:" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" 
{TEXT -1 5 "     " }{TEXT 270 0 "" }{TEXT 271 4 "plot" }{TEXT 272 2 "3
d" }{TEXT -1 2 "( " }{TEXT 273 4 "expr" }{TEXT -1 2 ", " }{TEXT 274 1 
"x" }{TEXT -1 8 "=range, " }{TEXT 275 0 "" }{TEXT 276 2 "y=" }{TEXT 
-1 19 "range [, options]);" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}{PARA 0 
"" 0 "" {TEXT -1 6 "where " }{TEXT 277 4 "expr" }{TEXT 281 1 " " }
{TEXT -1 24 "is a symbolic expression" }{TEXT 279 1 " " }{TEXT -1 48 "
which represents the function to be plotted and " }{TEXT 278 1 "x" }
{TEXT -1 5 " and " }{TEXT 282 0 "" }{TEXT 283 1 "y" }{TEXT 284 0 "" }
{TEXT -1 44 " are the two independent variables used in  " }{TEXT 280 
4 "expr" }{TEXT -1 25 "  to define the function." }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" 
{TEXT -1 0 "" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 4 "The " }{TEXT 285 0 "" }
{TEXT 286 6 "plot3d" }{TEXT 287 0 "" }{TEXT -1 238 " command will gene
rate a surface plot for the function over the rectangular range specfi
ed in the command statement.  The surface plot can be rotated, tipped \+
over and turned around to see the surface plot from all side and all v
iewpoints." }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT 
-1 278 "For each of the following functions provide a plot which shows
 the graph.  Choose reasonable values for the ranges of x and y.  Rota
te, where appropriate, to present a good view of the graph.  The last \+
two graphs are implicitly defined functions which require the Maple co
mmand " }{TEXT 297 0 "" }{TEXT 298 15 "implicitplot3d " }{TEXT 299 0 "
" }{TEXT -1 29 "which is part of the package " }{TEXT 300 0 "" }{TEXT 
301 5 "plots" }{TEXT 302 0 "" }{TEXT -1 1 "." }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT 
-1 0 "" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 5 "a.   " }{XPPEDIT 18 0 "z" "6#%\"
zG" }{TEXT -1 5 " =   " }{XPPEDIT 18 0 "cos(2*x-y^2)" "6#-%$cosG6#,&*&
\"\"#\"\"\"%\"xGF)F)*$%\"yGF(!\"\"" }}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "> " 0 "" 
{MPLTEXT 1 0 20 "f5:=   cos(2*x-y^2);" }}{PARA 11 "" 1 "" {XPPMATH 20 
"6#>%#f5G-%$cosG6#,&*&\"\"#\"\"\"%\"xGF+F+*$)%\"yGF*F+!\"\"" }}}
{EXCHG {PARA 0 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 32 "plot3d(f5(x,y),x=-5..5,y=-5.
.5);" }}{PARA 13 "" 1 "" {GLPLOT3D 385 385 385 {PLOTDATA 3 "6$-%%GRIDG
